Make sure that pip is installed already and install virtualenv:
$ sudo easy_install virtualenv pip

Create a virtual environment:
$ virtualenv name_of_your_yourenv

In the case you don't want to use global site packages directories, i.e. you wish to create a new env with individual modules and dependencies, you can use the command:
$ virtualenv --no-site-packages name_of_your_yourenv

Activate a virtual environment:
$ source yourenv/bin/activate

Deactivate the current virtual environment:
(name_of_your_yourenv)$ deactivate
